Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.97,0:00:07.30,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,You think Fujiki Kazuma will show up?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.13,0:00:09.19,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.61,0:00:13.82,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'm sure he'll show up at \NYoda Satomi-san's place.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.03,0:00:13.82,DCNameCards,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(398,1)\pos(323,295)\3c&HAF4B5C&}Yoda Satomi (25)\NOffice Worker
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.69,0:00:16.69,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Another stakeout?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.07,0:00:19.47,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.47,0:00:22.20,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,We saw a window with open blinds.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.20,0:00:24.96,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,How did you know it was a stakeout?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.42,0:00:27.09,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Call it a hunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.09,0:00:28.84,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We're in the same business, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.84,0:00:30.60,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Same business?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.60,0:00:31.71,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Is this him?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.71,0:00:32.54,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.54,0:00:34.63,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,They're looking for this guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.63,0:00:36.48,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,You can't just take that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.48,0:00:37.58,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Aww...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.58,0:00:39.09,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Which building are you watching?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.09,0:00:40.55,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Stop that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.55,0:00:41.56,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Aw, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.90,0:00:43.93,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So, what's the case about?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.48,0:00:47.18,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,We can't have them wandering around.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.18,0:00:48.72,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,If we want them to leave,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.72,0:00:51.31,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,we'll have to make them realize \Nthere's nothing for them to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.77,0:00:55.03,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Someone was injured during \Na robbery this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.87,0:00:59.90,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Beyond detective skills capable \Nof identifying the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.90,0:01:02.16,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,is the power to lead us \Nto what we should believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.16,0:01:03.90,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The Detective Boys show up at a stakeout!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.90,0:01:06.14,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Will they work together \Nto arrest the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.14,0:01:07.78,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.78,0:01:09.62,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.62,0:01:12.25,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.02,0:02:59.03,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(361,1)}Stakeout 2
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.67,0:02:55.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"Stakeout 2!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.43,0:03:02.41,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Not much was taken, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.74,0:03:04.89,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,The victim was a middle-aged man.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.89,0:03:08.05,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,He was knocked unconscious when struck \Non the head with a rod-like object.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.05,0:03:13.68,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We immediately determined the culprit was \NFujiki Kazuma, 25 years old, unemployed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.68,0:03:18.55,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But he hadn't returned home, and we \Ncouldn't determine where he had fled to.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.55,0:03:20.93,DCNote,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fs20\pos(51,120)\c&HDFE1DB&\3c&H777872&\blur1}BAR {\c&HA1C5D3&}Fukunishi
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.85,0:03:20.54,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,That's when we got some useful information.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.17,0:03:23.50,DCFlashback,BARTENDER,0000,0000,0000,,Fujiki is a self-centered guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.50,0:03:26.81,DCFlashback,BARTENDER,0000,0000,0000,,No matter who he dates, they \Nalways get sick of him eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.81,0:03:27.68,DCFlashback,BARTENDER,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.08,0:03:29.77,DCFlashback,FUJIKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yoda Satomi...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.77,0:03:33.21,DCFlashback,FUJIKI,0000,0000,0000,,She was probably the best woman for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.21,0:03:36.73,DCFlashback,FUJIKI,0000,0000,0000,,She loved me so much,\Nshe bawled when I left her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.73,0:03:37.90,DCFlashback,BARTENDER,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.65,0:03:41.57,DCNameCards,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(401,391)\3c&H8C4A70&\pos(313,296)}Fujiki Kazuma (25)\NUnemployed
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.90,0:03:41.17,DCFlashback,FUJIKI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I know. She's probably still waiting for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.17,0:03:43.10,DCFlashback,FUJIKI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'll get back together with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.45,0:03:45.20,DCFlashback,BARTENDER,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.59,0:03:48.41,DCFlashback,BARTENDER,0000,0000,0000,,It was two days ago that he said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.41,0:03:50.97,DCFlashback,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,So if he's wanted by the law...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.64,0:03:57.72,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure thought it was \Nlikely he'd go to see her,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.72,0:04:00.34,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,so we visited Yoda Satomi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.68,0:04:03.09,DCFlashback,SATOMI,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuma was involved in a robbery?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.09,0:04:06.41,DCFlashback,SATOMI,0000,0000,0000,,You want to know if he's contacted me? \NHe hasn't even called.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.96,0:04:10.90,DCFlashback,SATOMI,0000,0000,0000,,If he shows up here, I promise I'll call you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.90,0:04:13.35,DCFlashback,SATOMI,0000,0000,0000,,There's no point in running forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.92,0:04:16.78,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But we can't take her word for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.78,0:04:19.35,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Which is why we're conducting this stakeout,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.35,0:04:23.25,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,but there's no telling when \NFujiki Kazuma will show up,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.25,0:04:26.46,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,and there's no guarantee that he will at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.46,0:04:29.98,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing for \Nthe Detective Boys to do this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.98,0:04:32.12,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,There's no mystery to solve either.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.12,0:04:34.19,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.19,0:04:35.00,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.00,0:04:38.65,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible he won't show up in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.65,0:04:43.43,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,He could've already fled here \Nand be hiding inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.43,0:04:44.55,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.55,0:04:47.51,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, we considered that possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.51,0:04:51.42,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But when we visited, there were \Nno signs of anyone hiding.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.42,0:04:52.93,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.93,0:04:55.17,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,That makes it even stranger.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.17,0:05:02.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Fujiki-san seems like he'd immediately \Nrun to his ex Yoda Satomi-san for help,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.20,0:05:04.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,so why didn't he do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.51,0:05:09.34,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,We can't leave now. \NAfter all, there's a mystery here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.34,0:05:10.38,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.38,0:05:13.04,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,So you're staying, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.45,0:05:19.05,DCMain,SATOMI,0000,0000,0000,,What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.89,0:05:23.07,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,She looks like she's \Ndesperately trying to stay calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.07,0:05:26.05,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Her ex committed a crime, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.05,0:05:27.98,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It's been three years since they broke up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.98,0:05:32.91,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Does she still have feelings \Nfor Fujiki Kazuma, or...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.62,0:05:50.78,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,She's going out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.14,0:05:52.20,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Hold down the fort!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.20,0:05:52.94,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.94,0:05:54.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.50,0:05:57.49,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,She exited the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.49,0:05:58.67,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,She went that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.94,0:06:07.30,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,She's heading towards the station. \NI wonder who called her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.30,0:06:11.40,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It might've been Fujiki Kazuma \Nasking to meet her somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.40,0:06:13.02,DCMain,GIRLFRIEND,0000,0000,0000,,Give me back my money!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.02,0:06:15.12,DCMain,BOYFRIEND,0000,0000,0000,,I'll pay you back double, so go home!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.12,0:06:17.53,DCMain,GIRLFRIEND,0000,0000,0000,,You're gonna lose it all \Nplaying dice again, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.56,0:06:21.67,DCMain,BOYFRIEND,0000,0000,0000,,Stop that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.67,0:06:24.33,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't fight, and \Nyou shouldn't gamble either.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.33,0:06:25.71,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.71,0:06:26.52,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.52,0:06:27.82,DCMain,BOYFRIEND,0000,0000,0000,,He's a cop?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.82,0:06:31.21,DCMain,GIRLFRIEND,0000,0000,0000,,Did I say dice? I meant nice!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.11,0:06:33.09,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.92,0:06:46.26,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Lucky us.
